This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze the connotative meanings of language. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses distributional word representations and models for predicting connotation frames, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential use of connotation frames for analyzing biases in online news media, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
